PanLex Data License (OntoLex/TIAD edition)
==

PanLex is a project of <a href="http://longnow.org">The Long Now Foundation</a>, and provides <a href="https://panlex.org/snapshot/">CSV and JSON snapshots</a> of the PanLex Database, <a href="https://db.panlex.org">PanLex Lite</a>, and the <a href="https://db.panlex.org">PanLex Swadesh Lists</a> (“the Data”) under the <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/">CC0 1.0 Universal License</a>. 

The <a href="https://github.com/acoli-repo/acoli-dicts/tree/master/stable/panlex">RDF edition of the PanLex Database</a> has been created at the <a href="http://www.acoli.informatik.uni-frankfurt.de/">Applied Computational Linguistics (ACoLi) Lab, Goethe Universität Frankfurt</a>, and is also distributed under the <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/">CC0 1.0 Universal License</a>. 

You can copy, modify, and distribute the Data, even for commercial purposes, all without asking permission.

When using PanLex RDF data or referring to PanLex RDF, please cite either 
- both the websites <code>http://panlex.org</code> <i>and</i> <code>https://github.com/acoli-repo/acoli-dicts</code> or
- <i>both</i> the following papers:
	- Kamholz, David, Jonathan Pool, and Susan M. Colowick. 2014. PanLex: Building a Resource for Panlingual Lexical Translation. Proceedings of the 9th International Conference on Language Resources and Evaluation (LREC 2014). <code>http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/1029_Paper.pdf</code>
	- Christian Chiarcos, Christian Fäth, Maxim Ionov. subm. The ACoLi Dictionary Graph. Submitted to the 12th International Conference on Language Resources and Evaluation (LREC 2020)

Please direct all inquiries about the PanLex RDF conversion to <a href="mailto:christian.chiarcos@web.de">Christian Chiarcos</a>, and all inquiries about PanLex data to <a href="mailto:info@panlex.org">info@panlex.org</a>.

PanLex Data License (original data)
==
Note: The original license statement can be found under https://panlex.org/license/.

PanLex is a project of <a href="http://longnow.org">The Long Now Foundation</a>, and provides <a href="https://panlex.org/snapshot/">CSV and JSON snapshots</a> of the PanLex Database, <a href="https://db.panlex.org">PanLex Lite</a>, and the <a href="https://db.panlex.org">PanLex Swadesh Lists</a> (“the Data”) under the <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/">CC0 1.0 Universal License</a>. You can copy, modify, and distribute the Data, even for commercial purposes, all without asking permission.

When using PanLex data or referring to PanLex, please cite either the website (<code>http://panlex.org</code>) or the <a href="http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/1029_Paper.pdf">following paper</a>:

Kamholz, David, Jonathan Pool, and Susan M. Colowick. 2014. PanLex: Building a Resource for Panlingual Lexical Translation. Proceedings of the 9th International Conference on Language Resources and Evaluation (LREC 2014). <code>http://www.lrec-conf.org/proceedings/lrec2014/pdf/1029_Paper.pdf</code>

Please direct all inquiries to <a href="mailto:info@panlex.org">info@panlex.org</a>.
